<% content_for :title, "Quick start" %>

<section class="space-y-8">
  <header class="space-y-2">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Quick start</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-700">Install jwt-pq, sign your first post-quantum JWT, verify it.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">1. Install liboqs</h2>
    <p>jwt-pq binds to liboqs, an open-source implementation of NIST PQC algorithms.</p>
    <pre class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto"><code class="language-bash"># macOS
brew install liboqs

# Debian / Ubuntu
sudo apt-get install liboqs-dev</code></pre>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
      If liboqs is not on the default linker path, set
      <code>OQS_LIB</code> to the absolute path of the shared library before
      loading the gem.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">2. Install the gem</h2>
    <pre class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto"><code class="language-ruby">gem "jwt-pq", "~&gt; 0.5"

# Optional, only for hybrid mode
gem "ed25519", "~&gt; 1.4"</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">3. Sign and verify</h2>
    <pre class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto"><code class="language-ruby">require "jwt/pq"

key   = JWT::PQ::Key.generate(:ml_dsa_65)
token = JWT.encode({ sub: "u-1", iat: Time.now.to_i }, key, "ML-DSA-65")

payload, header = JWT.decode(
  token, key, true, algorithms: ["ML-DSA-65"]
)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">4. Export and distribute the public key</h2>
    <pre class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto"><code class="language-ruby">jwk = JWT::PQ::JWK.new(key).export
# =&gt; { kty: "AKP", alg: "ML-DSA-65", pub: "...", kid: "..." }

# Publish this somewhere verifiers can reach. jwt-pq can serve a remote
# JWKS and cache it:
loader   = JWT::PQ::JWKSLoader.new(url: "https://auth.example/.well-known/jwks.json")
verifier = loader.key_for(token_kid)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">5. Try it live</h2>
    <p>
      The <%= link_to "debugger", debugger_path, class: "underline" %> on this
      site runs the same gem. Click <em>Load ML-DSA-65 sample</em>, then
      <em>Verify</em>. The server round-trips the token through jwt-pq —
      there is no JavaScript reimplementation.
    </p>
  </section>
</section>
